ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
GOOD NEWS? The outcome of a huge case involving the Newhouse publishing empire 
and the IRS is said to have encouraged the Irvine Co. in its battle with 
heiress Joan Irvine Smith. . . . Newhouse heirs won a court victory over the 
IRS, which had valued the Newhouse chain at $2 billion and demanded $600 
million in taxes. . . . The Newhouse family said it was worth $250 million . . 
. . Similarly, Irvine Co. Chairman Donald L. Bren says the firm was only worth 
$1 billion when he bought it; Smith says it was worth $3 billion. . . . A court 
decision is expected soon. Kristina Lindgren and Mark Pinsky 
